Response:  We are given that Te Gen has 78 dollars and he wants to buy a bike for $15. So, we need to find out how many bikes Te Gen can buy with his money. To do this, we divide the amount of money Te Gen has ($78) by the cost of one bike ($15):

$78 / $15 = 5

So, Te Gen can buy 5 bikes with his $78.;

