Response:  If we have 140 groups of 187 cities each in a collection, then the total number of cities in that collection is:

140 x 187 = 23,600

So there are approximately 23,600 cities in the collection.;

Response:  We have 13 people in one group and they want to climb 4 mountains. Each person can carry only one mountain at a time. So, we need to divide them into groups of 4 so that each group can climb one mountain simultaneously. Now, let's calculate how many times these 13 people will be able to climb all 4 mountains if they work together:

Group 1: Climbs Mountain A Group 2: Climbs Mountain B Group 3: Climbs Mountain C Group 4: Climbs Mountain D

Since there are 4 mountains, each group will climb one mountain once. Therefore, the total number of times these 13 people will be able to climb all 4 mountains is 4 x 4 = 16 times.;
